Lecture 6: Sustainable Development Goals (SDGs) & Local Actions. The SDGs are a collection of 17 global goals designed to be a blueprint to achieve a better and more sustainable future for all. They were set up in 2015 by the United Nations General Assembly and are intended to be achieved by the year 2030. Goals include Goal 1: No Poverty, Goal 4: Quality Education, Goal 5: Gender Equality, and Goal 13: Climate Action. Localizing the SDGs means translating these global goals into concrete actions at the community, city, and regional levels.